{
  "texts": [
    "The input g-band σ DRW is randomly sampled from a log-uniform distribution between 0.02 mag and 0.2 mag, while the g-band τ DRW is set to a fiducial value of 100 days.",
    "The u-g and g-r lags are set to 1 day.",
    "We run EzTaoX on the first set of simulated light curves to extract the lag between the g-and r-band (τ gr), after subtracting the mean from each single-band light curve.",
    "The EzTaoX light curve model includes seven parameters: τ DRW, σ DRW, S g, S r, µ g, µ r, and τ gr.",
    "Here, S g and S r are the GP kernel scaling factors for g-and r-"
  ]
}